The Telegraph - Calcutta
 NCA to hold special camp
 BY A STAFF REPORTER Calcutta: In a bid to produce quality spinners and wicketkeepers, the National Cricket Academy (NCA) will hold a seven-day special camp in Bangalore. The camp will be held after the inter-zonal tournament of the academy in mid June. The limited-overs meet involving five zones will commence on May 27 and continue till June 15. After that meet gets over, the NCA selectors will shortlist a few spinners and wicketkeepers and try to sharpen their skills in the seven-day camp, a source said.  Copyright 
